This paper deals with the task of understanding 3D object structure from a single image, which is a core problem in computer vision. The proposed method involves estimating 2D keypoint heatmaps and 3D object skeletons and poses, which are key components of computer vision systems for object recognition and tracking. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also involves the use of synthetic 3D data to train the system, which is a common approach in computer graphics and computer vision research. Therefore, cs.GR (Graphics) is another likely sub-category. 

The paper proposes an end-to-end trainable framework that involves learning from both real and synthetic data, which is a common approach in machine learning research. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category. 

The paper also involves the use of knowledge learned from synthetic 3D shapes to estimate 3D object structure from real images, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence research. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves the use of 3D information for image retrieval, which is a common application of computer vision and multimedia research. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another likely sub-category.
